e needed for the task. The Cambodia issue changed all that. Singapore and her diplomats, by their conviction and doggedness, took the lead in galvanizing international and regional support to thwart the occupation of Cambodia as a fait accompli by Vietnam. This paper tells the inside story of how Singapore’s diplomats lobbied for ASEAN’s interests in various international fora at a critical time in the region’s history. The lessons learnt are still relevant today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh1 aDesker, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066299308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101240uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981476262540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814762625423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814762625.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066299-3  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  